  "prompt": "What are some of the best YoPappuSoDumb memes?",
  "response": "YoPappuSoDumb is a humorous spin-off of the classic \"Yo Mama\" jokes, focusing on playful jabs at someone's intelligence, often in an absurd and exaggerated way. Here are some of the best YoPappuSoDumb memes that have circulated on the internet:\n\n1. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he thought a quarterback was a refund.**\n   - This meme plays on the misunderstanding of a common term in American football, turning it into a hilariously literal interpretation.\n\n2. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he brought a spoon to the Super Bowl.**\n   - This one humorously conflates the Super Bowl football event with the idea of an actual bowl of food, showcasing a silly mix-up.\n\n3. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he got locked in a mattress store and slept on the floor.**\n   - This meme pokes fun at the idea of being surrounded by beds but choosing the floor, emphasizing a lack of common sense.\n\n4. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he thought Twitter was a social media platform for birds.**\n   - This plays on the literal interpretation of the name \"Twitter,\" showcasing a misunderstanding of modern technology.\n\n5. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he took a ruler to bed to see how long he slept.**\n   - A classic that highlights a literal interpretation of the phrase \"see how long,\" turning it into a ridiculous action.\n\n6. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he tried to climb Mountain Dew.**\n   - This meme plays with the concept of a soft drink brand name and turns it into a physical mountain, showing an amusing lack of understanding.\n\n7. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he put his phone on airplane mode and threw it out the window.**\n   - This one exaggerates the action of putting a phone on airplane mode into a literal interpretation of the term.\n\n8. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he thought a \"smartphone\" meant it did his homework.**\n   - This meme humorously showcases a misunderstanding of what \"smart\" means in the context of technology.\n\n9. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he stared at a can of orange juice because it said \"concentrate.\"**\n   - A classic that plays on the dual meaning of \"concentrate,\" leading to a silly visual of someone staring intently at a juice can.\n\n10. **Yo Pappu so dumb, he got fired from the M&M factory for throwing away all the W's.**\n    - This one humorously plays on the idea of someone not understanding that M&M's are simply called that, not containing any W's.\n\nThese memes are popular for their light-hearted nature and their ability to make people laugh at the absurdity of the situations described. Remember, the humor in these memes lies in their exaggeration and should be taken in good fun.",
